{"key":"processedPost-6082005","value":{"id":6082005,"first":6081031,"last":6082436,"when":1158773403,"utime":"09/20/06 08:30 PM","content":"While you can sometimes get away with it when the only thing exposed is a needle which can be inserted red hot through the verm barrier, don't try it open air with petri dishes or grain to grain transfers.<br /><br />I gave up on HEPA's in the house when I noticed one day when the sun was shining through a window, a gazzillion little dust particles dancing wildly in the turbulent air from the filter.  I would have expected the filter to remove those.   I shut down all the HEPA's in the house, and noticed a definite improvement in contamination rates in the fruiting chambers.---Bear in mind, I'm not talking about a laminar flow hood, which will clean the air in a room until there's practically no particles floating at all.  I'm only dissin' on the $100 units with paper filter elements they sell in department/hardware stores.<br />RR","title":"Re: does anyone here work completely open-air??"}}